Generation VII.Sun: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.
Generation VII.Moon: By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of calls and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.
Generation VII.Ultra Sun: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.
Generation VII.Ultra Moon: From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.

Generation IX.Scarlet: It flies around using a hundred different cries in various ways to declare its territory to others.
Generation IX.Violet: When it encounters foes, it launches the many seeds stored in its beak in a radial burst.
